   <titleInfo>
      <title>Letter, John Watkins in Knoxville, Tenn. to Sarah Probert in Pittsfield, Ohio, 1863 November 8</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>In this letter, dated November 8, 1863, from John Watkins in Knoxville, Tenn., to Sarah Probert in Pittsfield, Ohio, Watkins writes about the current prices for coffee, sugar, tea and other food products in Knoxville. He points out that one can trade coffee for almost any product. He also notes that the 19th Ohio Battery has buried its first soldier, who died of dysentery.</abstract>
